description: A JavaScript library for building user interfaces
author: Facebook
description_long: React is a JavaScript library for building user interfaces. It lets you compose complex UIs from small and isolated pieces of code called 'components'. React has a few different kinds of components, but we'll start with React.Component subclasses:

author: Evan You
description_long: Vue (pronounced /vjuÀê/, like view) is a progressive framework for building user interfaces. Unlike other monolithic frameworks, Vue is designed from the ground up to be incrementally adoptable.

author: Rich Harris
description_long: Svelte is a radical new approach to building user interfaces. Whereas traditional frameworks like React and Vue do the bulk of their work in the browser, Svelte shifts that work into a compile step that happens when you build your app.

author: Evan You
description_long: Vite (French word for 'quick', pronounced /vit/) is a build tool that aims to provide a faster and leaner development experience for modern web projects.

author: Vercel
description_long: Next.js is a React framework that gives you building blocks to create web applications. By framework, we mean Next.js handles the tooling and configuration needed for React, and provides additional structure, features, and optimizations for your application.
